  "description": "Garmon at the Tula wedding feast — the instrument of celebrations, spring festivals, village gatherings. Fast snappy attack (×0.5 model multiplier), open-box bandpass resonance, wide detune for the folk beating. Two slightly detuned PolyBLEP pulse oscillators produce the asymmetric reed buzz that garmon players call their signature sound. LFO1 at dance rate (4 Hz) for the characteristic wobble. This preset does not apologize for joy.",
